OL,4,CAmsterdam mayor apologises for city's
OL,5,Crole in slave trade
OL,6, The mayor of Amsterdam in the
OL,7, Netherlands has formally apologised for
OL,8, the city's role in slavery, as the
OL,9, country reckons with its colonial past.
OL,11,FFemke Halsema said it was "time to
OL,12,Fengrave the great injustice of colonial
OL,13,Fslavery into our city's identity".
OL,15,FThe apology came during an annual
OL,16,Fholiday that marks the end of slavery
OL,17,Fin Dutch colonies in the 1800s.
OL,19,FLast year the city council voted for an
OL,20,Fapology and an advisory panel has told
OL,21,Fthe national government to follow suit.
